# Anti-spoof models — attribution & provenance

`antispoof.onnx` and `antispoof_4.onnx` shipped here are ONNX conversions of
the MiniFASNet anti-spoofing models from:

    minivision-ai / Silent-Face-Anti-Spoofing
    https://github.com/minivision-ai/Silent-Face-Anti-Spoofing
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

Source weights:
    antispoof.onnx    ← 2.7_80x80_MiniFASNetV2.pth      (primary,   2.7× crop)
    antispoof_4.onnx  ← 4_0_0_80x80_MiniFASNetV1SE.pth  (secondary, 4.0× crop)

These are LinuxHello's own conversions (see `scripts/convert_antispoof.py`),
shipped so installation does not require a 2GB PyTorch toolchain. Because this
is a security-critical liveness gate, verify the files against `SHA256SUMS`
before trusting them — a tampered model that always outputs "real" would
silently defeat anti-spoofing. To rebuild from upstream yourself, run
`scripts/convert_antispoof.py` and compare the checksums.

A copy of the Apache 2.0 license is at https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.
